<ul><li>Anderson, Devery S. (Summer 2002), "<i>A History of </i>Dialogue<i>, Part Three: The Utah Experience, 1982-1989</i>" <i><a href="/wiki/Dialogue:_A_Journal_of_Mormon_Thought" title="Dialogue: A Journal of Mormon Thought">Dialogue: A Journal of Mormon Thought</a></i>, 35 (2).  Discusses the controversy that followed the publication of <a href="/wiki/Linda_King_Newell" title="Linda King Newell">Linda King Newell</a> and <a href="/wiki/Valeen_Tippetts_Avery" title="Valeen Tippetts Avery">Valeen Tippetts Avery</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/Mormon_Enigma:_Emma_Hale_Smith" class="mw-redirect" title="Mormon Enigma: Emma Hale Smith">Mormon Enigma: Emma Hale Smith, Prophet's Wife, Elect Lady, Polygamy's Foe</a></i> (New York: <a href="/wiki/Doubleday_(publisher)" title="Doubleday (publisher)">Doubleday</a>, 1984).</li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFArrington1998" class="citation book cs1">Arrington, Leonard J. (1998). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=KZr9lMg5zGwC"><i>Adventures of a Church Historian</i></a>. <a href="/wiki/Urbana,_Illinois" title="Urbana, Illinois">Urbana</a>: University of Illinois Press. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-252-02381-1" title="Special:BookSources/0-252-02381-1"><bdi>0-252-02381-1</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Adventures+of+a+Church+Historian&amp;rft.place=Urbana&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft.isbn=0-252-02381-1&amp;rft.aulast=Arrington&amp;rft.aufirst=Leonard+J.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DKZr9lMg5zGwC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormonism+and+history" class="Z3988"></span></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFArrington2005" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Leonard_J._Arrington" title="Leonard J. Arrington">Arrington, Leonard J.</a> (2005). "Faith and Intellect as Partners in Mormon History". <i>The Collected Leonard J. Arrington Mormon History Lectures</i>. Special Collections &amp; Archives, <a href="/wiki/Utah_State_University" title="Utah State University">Utah State University</a> Libraries. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-87421-598-6" title="Special:BookSources/0-87421-598-6"><bdi>0-87421-598-6</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Faith+and+Intellect+as+Partners+in+Mormon+History&amp;rft.btitle=The+Collected+Leonard+J.+Arrington+Mormon+History+Lectures&amp;rft.pub=Special+Collections+%26+Archives%2C+Utah+State+University+Libraries&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.isbn=0-87421-598-6&amp;rft.aulast=Arrington&amp;rft.aufirst=Leonard+J.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormonism+and+history" class="Z3988"></span></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Davis_Bitton" title="Davis Bitton">Davis Bitton</a> (1994) "The Ritualization of Mormon History," in <i>The Ritualization of Mormon History and Other Essays</i> (Urbana: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>), 171–187.</li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBushman2007" class="citation book cs1">Bushman, Richard (2007). <i>On the Road with Joseph Smith: An Author's Diary</i>. Salt Lake City: Greg Kofford Books.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=On+the+Road+with+Joseph+Smith%3A+An+Author%27s+Diary&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.pub=Greg+Kofford+Books&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.aulast=Bushman&amp;rft.aufirst=Richard&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormonism+and+history" class="Z3988"></span></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Terryl_L._Givens" class="mw-redirect" title="Terryl L. Givens">Terryl L. Givens</a> (2007), <i>People of Paradox:  A History of Mormon Culture.</i> (<a href="/wiki/Oxford_University_Press" title="Oxford University Press">Oxford University Press</a>). <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-19-516711-2" title="Special:BookSources/0-19-516711-2">0-19-516711-2</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Richard_and_Joan_Ostling" title="Richard and Joan Ostling">Richard N. Ostling and Joan K. Ostling</a> (1999), "Faithful History," in <i>Mormon America: The Power and the Promise</i> (<a href="/wiki/HarperSanFrancisco" class="mw-redirect" title="HarperSanFrancisco">HarperSanFrancisco</a>), 238–58.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/D._Michael_Quinn" title="D. Michael Quinn">D. Michael Quinn</a> (1994), <i><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.today/20061021174136/http://www.signaturebooks.com/hier1.htm">The Mormon Hierarchy: Origins of Power</a></i> (Salt Lake City: <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>).</li>
<li>George D. Smith, ed. (1992), <i><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20101127142240/http://signaturebookslibrary.org/faithful/intro.htm">Faithful History: Essays on Writing Mormon History</a></i> (Salt Lake City: <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>).</li>
<li>Gary Topping (2003), <i>Utah Historians and the Reconstruction of Western History</i>  (Norman: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Oklahoma_Press" title="University of Oklahoma Press">University of Oklahoma Press</a>) <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-8061-3561-1" title="Special:BookSources/0-8061-3561-1">0-8061-3561-1</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Ronald_W._Walker" title="Ronald W. Walker">Ronald W. Walker</a>, David J. Whittaker, and <a href="/wiki/James_B._Allen_(historian)" title="James B. Allen (historian)">James B. Allen</a> (2001), <i>Mormon History</i> (Urbana: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>) <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-252-02619-5" title="Special:BookSources/0-252-02619-5">0-252-02619-5</a></li></ul>
